{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01KhaAQ3uWqShT4JgtLJmi7R","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the logs but no access log entries from my curl requests. This is strange. Let me check:\n\n1. Is the curl-test pod still running?\n2. Is the ingress-nginx controller still routing requests?\n3. Are the access logs being written somewhere else?\n\nActually, the issue might be that nginx is still using the OLD log format for the access log. Looking at the nginx.conf excerpt I retrieved earlier, the log format is being correctly set. But wait - after a nginx reload (not restart), the old workers continue processing existing connections, and new workers take over for new connections. The new workers should use the new log format.\nThe nginx.conf already has the OpenTelemetry fields in the log format, so that's not the issue. But I'm not seeing recent access log entries, which is odd. Maybe the OTel errors are overwhelming the log buffer and preventing the access logs from being captured.\n\nLet me check the curl-test pod to see if my requests are actually reaching the controller. I ran a curl command using HTTP to the ingress controller service with the Host header set to otel.example.com, but I should verify if that request is even getting through.\n\nThe 404 response makes sense if that path doesn't have a backend, but I'm not seeing corresponding access log entries, which is odd. Maybe the logs are buffered or stored elsewhere. Let me try following the logs in real-time to catch fresh entries.\n\nI'm also wondering if the OTel initialization failed when the nginx workers started, which would explain why the traces aren't being exported properly and the module might be operating in a no-op mode. The `$opentelemetry_trace_id` variable comes from the nginx module itself, so if the exporter didn't initialize correctly, these variables could be empty even though they're being populated.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1732,"cache_read_input_tokens":63479,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1732},"output_tokens":35,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0969516e-3362-440b-9982-8ea728415013","uuid":"3adc6091-95a8-49ec-8798-c663b9141993","request_id":"req_011Cc5BaQPj8kZChmatm7Kcm"}
