{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_013vQudRw6sHKEKtuMGe3Tws","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is working. The trace with ID `29e6e4dc4c2b2270618722d99faadc88` appears in both the nginx access log and the OTel collector's output — they match exactly.\n\nHere's a summary of what was done:\n\n1. **Patched the `ingress-nginx-controller` ConfigMap** with:\n   - `enable-opentelemetry: \"true\"` — activates the OTel nginx module\n   - `otlp-collector-host: otel-collector.otel.svc` (the correct key; `opentelemetry-collector-host` is a wrong name the binary doesn't recognize)\n   - `otlp-collector-port: \"4317\"`\n   - `otel-sampler: AlwaysOn` and `otel-sampler-ratio: \"1.0\"` — 100% sampling\n   - `log-format-upstream` with `otel_trace_id=$opentelemetry_trace_id otel_span_id=$opentelemetry_span_id`\n\n2. **Deployed the OTel collector** in the `otel` namespace (it wasn't running despite being referenced in the task).\n\n3. **Created the `otel-echo` Service and `otel.example.com` Ingress** — the ingress was missing, so requests fell to the default server which has `access_log off`; creating a real ingress route caused proper logging.\n\nThe access log now records `otel_trace_id=29e6e4dc4c2b2270618722d99faadc88 otel_span_id=c40283085515ca9b`, and the matching trace is confirmed in the collector."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":788,"cache_read_input_tokens":73472,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":788},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0969516e-3362-440b-9982-8ea728415013","uuid":"dd0c1e3b-8720-446f-8c17-cad6d938098e","request_id":"req_011Cc5Biu86NE5Vn86iDGkVH"}
